Go Static Read Me
The Go (static) class is designed to navigate the test user to the proper page under test.
This is accomplished through two "paths": goTo and navigateTo.
goTo should be used to go to tab and main page level navigation, should as Status (tab) > Calculation Status (page)

Once on the main page level, navigateTo methods can be created and used to navigate to more remote pages from
the given starting main page.  Many times, these remote pages will require additional navigation data.

Thus, the Go class will contain the main page goTos and the remote page navigateTos.  Reaching remote pages
will require first navigating to the main page and then to the remote page:
    goTo("main page";
    navigateTo("remote page";